Common Terms
•	Repository (Repo): A collection of files and their version history.
•	Commit: A snapshot of your code at a particular time.
•	Branch: A parallel version of your code.
•	Merge: Combining different branches together.
•	Clone: Copying a remote repository to your local machine.
•	Pull: Fetch + Merge changes from remote to local.
•	Push: Sending local commits to a remote repository.




